5|$|Elvis Presley was {{inducted}} <b>into</b> <b>the</b> <b>Army</b> on March 24, 1958. During the final {{months of his}} service, Presley began experimenting with new material in anticipation of his return to recording. Friend Charlie Hodge taught him to improve his breathing and expand his vocal range, and Presley added a full octave. He was discharged on March 5, 1960.|$|E
