5000|$|McCarthy wrote {{a letter}} to Secretary of <b>the</b> <b>Army</b> Robert T. Stevens calling for Peress to be court-martialed. He called for an {{investigation}} <b>into</b> <b>the</b> <b>Army's</b> handling of Peress' commissioning and promotion. [...] Stevens believed that Peress' refusals to answer the Committee's questions did not provide grounds for court-martial and approved Peress' discharge on February 2.|$|R
